File: Bidvest Wits team. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Football Players’ Union has written to the Premier Soccer League about the sale of Bidvest Wits. This follows claims that players and coach Gavin Hunt found out about the sale through the media. READ: PSL desperate for games to resume Tshakhuma Tsha Madzhivhandila announced on Saturday that they completed a takeover deal and plan to move the team to Limpopo next season, pending approval. The union's president has now written to the PSL seeking clarity about the matter.